Purposes for Collection and Use
Identifiers
We collect your IP address and assign a unique cookie to your browser.
If you create a healthcare professional account we collect your first and last name, email address, and password. You may provide additional personal information like your phone number, date of birth and  last four digits of your social security number.  We assign your account a unique identifying number.
If you log in with a Facebook or LinkedIn account, we may receive your name, profile picture, age, language, email address, and friend / connections list.
We use Personal Information to provide our services to you.
We use cookie and IP information to enable you to access our platform, provide basic functionality (like logging in or accessing content), secure our platform, protect against fraudulent logins, and detect and prevent abuse or unauthorized use of your account.
We use IP and Personal Information derived from cookies to identify new and returning visitors, and their usage and access preferences. We may also personalize your experience (for instance, to recognize you by name when you return to our platform, to present content in the language of your browser, or to promote certain content or features to you).
We use your contact  information to communicate with you by email, text messages or telephone, including on behalf of potential employers. We may send you messages about your account and soliciting your feedback via surveys.
