Included in pay stub used for the verification of employment and hiring through the Vivian platform.
Internet or other electronic network activity information
We collect usage statistics about your interactions with our platform, including the last page you were on before clicking to our platform, pages you visited, content you accessed, time you spent on pages, features you used, your search queries, click data, online chat communications, and the date and time of these activities.
We also log job applications you consult and apply for and information you provide (such as completed skills checklists), your interactions with recruiters, potential employers, or Vivian staff, including via chat, email, SMS messages, and push notifications, and how you respond or interact with these messages.
We use this Personal Information to analyze platform usage. This enables us to improve the design, content and services on our platform.
We measure our platform usage and performance data such as visit counts, traffic sources. This helps us test different versions of Vivian.com to see which features or content users prefer and determine which email messages are opened.
We also use this Personal Information to determine healthcare job market trends based on what content is consumed, what job searches are performed, and other aggregated platform usage data. This helps us inform and improve our services to healthcare professionals and employers, and to develop new products, services, and features.
We also observe usage trends to secure our platform, prevent fraud and abuse.
Geolocation data
We also collect your approximate geographic location, like country, city, and approximate geographic coordinates, calculated based on your IP address.
We may send you our customers job listings based on your region and tailor the content presented to you based on your region.
Professional or employment-related information
If you create a healthcare professional account you may submit to us your work history, references, education, certifications and other professional information.
We may also receive your past or current compensation information.
We may send you our customers job listings based on your past jobs, work experience and qualifications.
Upon your instruction, or when you apply for a job, we disclose your work credentials with the recruiter or potential employer, so they can consider your application.
We anonymize and aggregate healthcare professional compensation information to provide pay insights and recommendations to healthcare professionals, healthcare facilities and staffing agencies.
Non-public education information
If you create a healthcare professional account you may submit to us your education information and certifications.
We send you our customers job listings based on your education and certifications.
Upon your instruction, or when you apply for a job, we disclose your education and certifications with the recruiter or potential employer, so they can consider your application.
We collect the Personal Information described in the chart above from the sources described in the
How We Collect Your Personal Information
Section of this Privacy Policy.
Sales and Sharing
We Share and Sell Identifiers, Geolocation data, and Internet and other electronic network activity with Third Party advertisers and analytics partners to target ads to you based on your activities on the Vivian platform. This is to allow our advertising partners to target advertisements to you when you are visiting third party websites via cookies and other browser identifiers.
Rights Under the CCPA
If you are a California resident, you have certain rights under the CCPA. These include:
Right to Know or Access to the Personal Information we have Collected about You
As a California resident, you have the right to request to know more about the categories and specific pieces of Personal Information that we have Collected about you and access a portable copy of your Personal Information. Specifically, you have to right to know:
The categories of Personal Information we have Collected about you
The categories of sources from which the Personal Information was Collected
Our Business or Commercial Purposes for Collecting, Selling, or Sharing your Personal Information
The categories of Third Parties to which we disclosed your Personal Information
The categories of Personal Information we Sold or Shared about you and the categories of Third Parties to which each category of Personal Information was Sold or Shared
The categories of Personal Information we disclosed about you for a Business Purpose and the categories of recipients to which it was disclosed
The specific pieces of Personal Information we have Collected about you
Requests of this nature may be made no more than twice in a 12-month period.
Right to Deletion
As a California resident, you have the right to request that we delete the Personal Information that we have Collected directly from you and are currently maintaining. Please note, however, that we may have a legal basis for retaining certain Personal Information under the CCPA, despite your request.
Right to Correct Personal Information
As a California resident, you may request that Vivian correct Personal Information that we maintain about you if you believe such Personal Information is inaccurate. We may request documentation from you in connection with your request. We will also require you (or your agent) to be verified before honoring your correction requests. Upon receipt of a verifiable request to correct inaccurate Personal Information, we will use commercially reasonable efforts to correct the personal information as you direct. You can also correct certain Personal Information that we maintain about you by logging into your Healthcare Professional account or your Employer/Recruiter Account.
Right to Limit our Use of Your Sensitive Personal Information
Vivian does not collect or use Sensitive Personal Information.
Right to Non-Discrimination
Vivian will not discriminate against you or penalize you in any way if you choose to exercise any of the privacy rights described above.
Right to Opt Out of the Sale or Sharing of Personal Information
We only engage in Sales and Sharing via tracking technologies, such as cookies and software development kits (SDKs) through the Vivian platform. You have the right to opt-out of the Sale or Sharing of your Personal Information in the context of cookies or other tracking technologies.
Exercising Rights under the CCPA
To exercise any of the rights under the CCPA listed above, contact us at
support@vivian.com
or write to us at 100 Pine Street, Suite 1250, PMB A140, San Francisco, CA 94111. The CCPA allows you to designate an authorized agent to make these requests on your behalf. For your protection, we may require that the request be sent through the email address associated with your account, and we may need to verify you and/or your agent’s identity before fulfilling your request.
To opt out of Sale or Sharing via cookies or other tracking technologies, please see instructions in the
How to Opt Out of Selling, Sharing and Targeted Advertising (CA and VA)
Section below. You may also opt out of the Sale or Sharing of your Personal Information via cookies or tracking technologies through an opt-out preference signal. In order to process your request through an opt-out preference signal, you must use a browser supporting the preference signal. If you choose to use an opt-out preference signal, you will need to turn it on for each browser and each device you use.
Notice of Financial Incentive
If we offer any financial incentives in connection with sweepstakes and other giveaways, we will provide a notice of financial incentive disclosure, including the material terms associated with each financial incentive we offer at the time you consent to participate in a sweepstakes or other giveaway. For additional information on contests or sweepstakes, please refer to the
Personal Information We Collect
Section.
California Shine the Light
California's "Shine the Light" law (Civil Code Section § 1798.83) permits users of our platform that are California residents to request certain information regarding our disclosure of personal information to third parties for their direct marketing purposes. To make such a request, please send an email to
support@vivian.com
or write us at 100 Pine Street, Suite 1250, PMB A140, San Francisco, CA 94111, with the phrase “California Shine the Light”and include your mailing address, state of residence (California), and email address.
Virginia Residents
This section applies to Virginia Consumers as defined by the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (“VCDPA”) that use our platform. Capitalized terms defined in the VCDPA that are used in this section shall have the same meaning as in the VCDPA.
You can learn more about the Personal Data we Process in the
Personal Information We Collect
Section and the purpose for processing such Personal Data in the
How we Use your Personal Information
Section of this Privacy Policy.  You can also learn more about our disclosure of Personal Data and the categories of Third Parties we disclose Personal Data to in the
With Whom and Why we Share your Personal Information
section of this Privacy Policy.
We also Process your Personal Data for Targeted Advertising. You have the right to opt-out of the Processing of your Personal Data for Targeted Advertising, as described below.
Rights under the VCDPA
If you are a Virginia Consumer, subject to certain conditions and restrictions set out in the VCDPA and other applicable laws, you have the following rights with regard to your Personal Data:
Right to Access. You have the right to know the Personal Data that we may hold about you and access such Personal Data.
Right to Correct. You have the right to request that we correct inaccuracies in your Personal Data.
Right to Delete. You have the right to request that we delete certain  Personal Data that we have collected from or obtained about you.
Right to Opt-Out of Sales. We do not Sell your Personal Data as defined under the VCDPA.
Right to Opt-Out of Profiling. We do not engage in profiling that results in decisions that produce legal or similarly significant effects, and as such this right is not applicable.
Right to Appeal. If you are unsatisfied with our actions related to the exercise of one of your privacy rights above, you may appeal our decision.
Right to Opt-Out of Targeted Advertising. You may request that we stop disclosures of your Personal Data for Targeted Advertising.
Exercising Rights under the VCDPA
To opt out of Targeted Advertising, please see instructions in the
How to Opt Out of Selling, Sharing and Targeted Advertising (CA and VA)
Section below.
To exercise any of the other rights under the VCDPA listed above, contact us at
hello@vivian.com
or write to us at 100 Pine Street, Suite 1250, PMB A140, San Francisco, CA 94111. Please note that, depending on the nature of your request, you may be asked to provide information to verify your identity before your request can be processed. We will confirm receipt of your request and respond to your request as soon as we reasonably can and no later than legally required.
You may exercise your rights under the VCDPA no more than twice in a 12-month period. If you choose to exercise any of the privacy rights described above, you will not receive discriminatory treatment from us.
